{
  "texts": [
    "We often consider mAP@0.5 which is computed by using the IoU threshold 0.5 to define a match but just as well we could compute mAP@0.75 or mAP@0.9, or mAP@[0.5:0.95] which is the the mean value of mAP@0.5, mAP@0.55,.",
    ", mAP@0.95.",
    "The metric mAP@0.9 is more strict than mAP@0.5 given it requires greater overlap for the potential matches and is therefore suitable for situations where the predicted bounding box locations need to be very exact 10.",
    "Information search and retrieval is a significant task in ML research.",
    "The ability to retrieve only relevant results from large image-or text-based databases is crucial for these databases to be actually useful."
  ]
}